						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājadēva I: (?) Year 4 = 988-89 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is also slightly damaged. It records a gift made by Malāḍuḍaiyāṉ [••• •••] of 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> for 12 <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamps for burning during the evening service in the temple of the god Tiruppulippagavar Āḻvār of Śiṟṟiṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Kuṟukkaik-kūṟṟam in Malāḍu. The gift was accepted by the temple managers who had agreed to burn the lamps accordingly.</p>						

						</summary>
